        <div class="disclosure-box disclosure-box--info">
          <strong>🔗 Affiliate Disclosure</strong>
          <p style="margin-top:var(--space-sm);">Some links in this guide are affiliate links. If you buy something through them, we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. We only recommend products we've thoroughly researched and genuinely believe in.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Let's be honest — nobody plans for cable spaghetti. You set up your monitor, plug in your laptop, add a desk lamp, phone charger, maybe a second monitor, and before you know it, there's a knotted mess under your desk that looks like a prop from a sci-fi movie.</p>

        <p>Cable management is one of those things you ignore until you can't anymore. Then one day you trip on a dangling cord, or you're on a video call and someone spots the nest of wires behind your monitor, and you think: <em>I need to fix this.</em></p>

        <p>Good news: you don't need to spend a fortune or be a professional organizer to get it done. The right combination of cheap clips, a decent cable tray, and a little patience will make your desk look cleaner and work better. This guide covers everything — the $10 fixes, the pro-tier solutions, the DIY hacks, and exactly what order to do it all in.</p>

