        <h2 id="why-it-matters">Why Cable Management Actually Matters</h2>

        <p>It's easy to write off cable management as an aesthetic thing — something for Instagram workspaces and people with too much time. But there are real, practical reasons to clean up your cables.</p>

        <h3>It's a Fire Hazard (Seriously)</h3>
        <p>Dust builds up on cables, especially behind desks where nobody vacuums. That's a problem because dust is flammable, and cables — especially power bricks and extension cords — generate heat. A dense pile of tangled cords traps heat and provides fuel. It's not common, but cable-related fires do happen. The National Fire Protection Association doesn't break out 
